more wing area, so a large helicopter would

00:00:39.240 --> 00:00:40.240
need as long a rotor as possible.

00:00:40.240 --> 00:00:41.240
But this creates all sorts of problems.

00:00:41.240 --> 00:00:42.780
For example, the tips of the rotor blades
can’t go faster than the speed of sound

00:00:42.780 --> 00:00:45.550
or the turbulence will make the blades less
efficient.

00:00:45.550 --> 00:00:48.480
The longer the blades get, the faster the
tips travel.

00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:52.329
If the helicopter has an enormous and fast
spinning rotor, it won’t be able to fly

00:00:52.329 --> 00:00:57.050
very fast because the blade that’s spinning
in the same direction the helicopter is moving

00:00:57.050 --> 00:01:01.649
